  "text": "Once the raw data is acquired, command and control teams are limited by whatever details are visible in the two-dimensional image. Beyond zooming and cropping, the viewer cannot interact with the image and hence, little information can be gathered. 3D Reconstruction (3DR) is the computer vision technique that creates a graphical model from 2D images [CITATION_1] .",
